Summary:
This transient deck shows a repeated RC ramp waveform. A pulse source repeatedly charges and discharges the capacitor through the resistor, producing a sawtooth-like output.
It is a time-domain example, not a frequency-domain filter plot.

Line-by-line:
`R1 N002 N001 10` is the series resistor.
`C1 N002 0 10m` is the capacitor to ground.
`V1 N001 0 PULSE(-200 200 0 500m 0.001u 0.001u 500m 10)` is the pulse source.
`.tran 10s` runs the simulation long enough to show the repeated ramps.
The comment names the waveform as sawtooth.

Netlist meaning:
The capacitor voltage changes gradually because the resistor limits current.
Each pulse edge restarts the ramp in the opposite direction.
